description:
This rate must be used in combination with Schedule PI Off Season. This schedule is applicable and restricted to pumping of ground water for drainage or irrigation for the purpose of Agricultural/Livestock Production within the irrigation service area boundary where such pumping is eligible to be served with electricity sold to the District by the City and County of San Francisco pursuant to Section 9(l) of the federal Raker Act. This schedule is applicable on an annual basis only.
On Season:
Connected Load Charge, per HP: $ 1.66
Energy Charge per kWh $ 0.0716
Off Season:
Energy Charge, per kWh $ 0.1654
name: Schedule PI Restricted Irrigation Pumping(On Season)
